<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-628-369  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 628 369.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  Nov 14 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Comdex: language translator software. (Globalink's GTS) (productannouncement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Zucker, Paul.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Globalink Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   GTS (Computer program) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Software PublishersProduct IntroductionSoftware packagesLanguage Translation.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>COMDEX: LANGUAGE TRANSLATOR SOFTWARE 11/14/90 LAS VEGAS, NEVADA, U.S.A., 1990NOV 14 (NB) -- A $998 PC-based language translator program shown at Comdex isbeing billed as a translator cheaper to employ than humans, according todeveloper Globalink.andP;  GTS, for Globalink Foreign Language Translator, takesASCII files in English or a number of foreign languages, and translates themat up to 20,000 words per hour.andP;  However, the company emphasizes that theprogram must be seen as an aid to human-supervised translation, not areplacement for it.andM;Users must purchase a version per direction -- English to French is $998, andso is French to English.andP;  Other languages include German, Spanish, Russianand Chinese.andP;  Globalink told Newsbytes that the program does much more thanliteral translation, and is able to interpret idiom, context andsubject-specific text.andP;  Where sentence structure differs between languages,the output is correct, not stilted.andM;Already, a number of leading international business and diplomatic users haveadopted and praised the system, quoting speed improvements of as much as 80percent.andP;  The dictionary, rather than being fixed, is constantly upgradableby the user, with modules available for specific areas such as computers, lawand commerce.andM;(Paul Zucker/19901114/Contact: Globalink 703-2735600)</TEXT></DOC>